or Diocletian in   ad  303 . She became a very popular saint in the Middle Ages. Her name was early associated with Latin <i>agnus</i> ‘lamb’, leading to the consistent dropping of the initial <i>H-</i> and to her representation in art accompanied by a lamb. The colloquial form <i>Annes</i> led to some confusion with <i>Ann(e)</i> in earlier centuries. Frequent in the medieval period, the name was revived in the 19th century, and has been especially popular in Scotland.  See also  Annis ."],"variants":[]},{"name":"De","type":"FIRST","attribution":"Dictionary of First Names © Patrick Hanks and Flavia Hodges 1990, 2003, 2006.","meanings":["‘Attainment’."],"variants":[]}],"lifeSummary":"Agnes De Covele was born about 1120, in England, United Kingdom. She married Roger BROOKS about 1139. They were the parents of at least 1 son."},"et":{"Abt 1120–":"umbes 1120–Surnud","–Male":"Surnud","1140–Male":"1140–Surnud","1120–Female":"1120–Surnud","Abt 1120":"umbes 1120","ABT 1140":"umbes 1140","Abt 1139":"umbes 1139","1120":"1120","1140":"1140","Of,,, England":"Inglismaa, United Kingdom"},"fi":{"Abt 1120–":"noin 1120–Kuollut","–Male":"Kuollut","1140–Male":"1140–Kuollut","1120–Female":"1120–Kuollut","Abt 1120":"noin 1120","ABT 1140":"noin 1140","Abt 1139":"noin 1139","1120":"1120","1140":"1140","Of,,, England":"Englanti, Yhdistynyt kuningaskunta"},"fr":{"Abt 1120–":"environ 1120–Décédée","–Male":"Décédé","1140–Male":"1140–Décédé","1120–Female":"1120–Décédée","Abt 1120":"environ 1120","ABT 1140":"environ 1140","Abt 1139":"environ 1139","1120":"1120","1140":"1140","Of,,, England":"Angleterre, Royaume-Uni","lifeSummary":"Agnes De Covele est née environ 1120, à Angleterre, Royaume-Uni. Elle a épousé Roger BROOKS environ 1139. Ils ont eu au moins 1 fils."},"de":{"Abt 1120–":"um 1120–Verstorben","–Male":"Verstorben","1140–Male":"1140–Verstorben","1120–Female":"1120–Verstorben","Abt 1120":"um 1120","ABT 1140":"um 1140","Abt 1139":"um 1139","1120":"1120","1140":"1140","Of,,, England":"Eng